In order to install MySQL server follow this tutorial:
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql-yum-repo-quick-guide/en/

To open the MySQL shell on the current machine:
$ mysql -u root -p
> show databases;
> use 'enter name of database';
> show tables;

Here is a tutorial for MySQL:
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/tutorial.html

To install the python mysql connector library type:
$ sudo pip install mysql-connector-python

Scripts have to be run through terminal in order to use the python MySQL library
